relate-context

DESCRIPTION
  The context can represent the currently connected provider or DBMS.

USAGE
  relate context apply (<key> <value> | --file=<path>)
  relate context reset [<key>]
  relate context current

OPTIONS
  --file=<path>    File to load context from.

NOTES
  apply:
    It should be possible to pass the context via STDIN.
  reset:
    If no key is specified, all information is reset.

EXAMPLE
  $ relate context apply --file=graph-project
  $ relate db list
  $ relate db create foo
  $ relate context reset
